job_description:
Your Impact
You will give direction to large projects and make the right choices. You will substantiate these on the basis of your insights and knowledge. And more importantly, you will put them into practice. You will work primarily on projects in the industrial sector, large government institutions or for major Dutch banks. There you show your added value as an Architect and help clients with your expertise by setting out the lines for High Performance teams. Work you can be proud of! That is important to us.


Working at the largest architecture community in the Netherlands;
50 professionals united and connected in a team with architects at different levels and with various areas of expertise, and part of Ordina Digital;

Performing a wide variety of assignments for different types of clients;
Realizing visible innovations at the largest companies in the Netherlands;
The opportunity to develop yourself into a full-fledged architect through a customized training program.

Where you're going to get started
At IT & Architecture Transformation, you work together with over 50 architects in various disciplines. We know the developments in the market, recognize new trends and offer services that fit both the client's needs and Ordina's proposition. We advise customers on the design, implementation, operation and organization of their IT workflows in order to help them digitize in the best possible way. We translate our customer's strategy and plans into a future-proof and, where necessary, agile design of the IT landscape. In doing so, we guide the realization into a working whole. At Ordina IT & Architecture Transformation there is plenty of room to develop yourself. Continuous learning so that we always stay ahead together.


This is you
You think ahead. You're curious. You want to understand how things work. You have vision and like to work with other stakeholders to figure out what solutions will look like. You are able to work at a high level of abstraction. You have experience in designing solutions and monitoring that they are well realized.

And last but not least: you are ready for the next step in your career.


Ambition to take the next step in your career and develop yourself as an architect;
A completed HBO or WO education, preferably in business administration or a technical field;
Strong social and communication skills;
Excellent command of the Dutch language both verbally and in writing;
Some experience with designing solutions: for example, designing processes, applications or data models.

Benefits
A good salary that grows with your experience within the Young Professional program;
Work from home opportunities, if it suits our client;
Extensive training opportunities at the Ordina Academy;
You will join a training group of several Young Professionals. Together you will attend training courses, share experiences, play a game of table soccer and have a drink afterwards;
20 statutory days off per year and 7 additional days off through flex benefits;
Choice between a company car or a travel allowance.


Everyone is welcome to apply. Because we believe in the power of diversity and value inclusion. After all, the best ideas and smartest solutions arise in diverse teams. That is exactly why we pay so much attention to the composition of our high performance teams. So that you feel at home and can get the best out of yourself.

At Anywhere365, customer centricity and customer experience are essential to us, and to ensure this, our Support team is on a mission to push customer support to the next level while ensuring a positive experience in resolving the most challenging issues for global customers. As an employer, Anywhere365 has been recognized as a “Great Place to Work” and we are immensely proud of this accomplishment! This is a great time to join us.
Currently, we are looking for a Creative Graphic Designer, who will join us in our globally shared and exciting challenge to grow the value of our market-leading solution even further. Our Marketing team is fully embedded in various creative initiatives, from ensuring our designs create a recognizable and memorable brand experience. We are on a mission to increase customer success and optimize the customer experience.
The role

As a creative graphic designer who loves to create visually stunning designs that drive results, you will focus on creating visually appealing designs that align with our brand and marketing goals, as well as establishing and optimizing customer success initiatives to drive customer satisfaction and retention.
To be successful in this role, candidates must possess the following skills:
We are looking for a Graphic designer who has:
Strong portfolio demonstrating creative and effective design solutions with a focus on marketing and customer success.
Proficiency in design software such as Adobe Creative Suite (Photoshop, Illustrator, InDesign) and other design tools.
Knowledge of design principles such as color theory, typography, composition, and layout.
 Manage multiple projects simultaneously and meet tight deadlines.
Excellent communication and collaboration skills.
Ability to work independently and as part of a team.

We pick character over skills

Can you convince us that you are:

Proactive and detail-oriented;

Eager to learn, develop and share proactively share knowledge;
You are cooperative, curious, result driven, and a self-starter;
Excellent communication skills; fluent in English;
Responsive to change. No, let’s rephrase that: you thrive on change!

What do we offer you in the Netherlands?

25 holiday days annually
Working from home allowance;
Home office set-up (chair, desk – these will be yours!);
Secured laptop, docking station, mouse, keyboard, extra screen, and headset;
Flexibility from where you work;
Pension scheme;
Headspace subscription.

This is us:

Did we already mention that Anywhere365 is a successful, rapidly expanding international scale-up? Well, we are. And so, we have a headquarter office that will give you goose bumps. As we should. But since remote working is the current standard, and we hate cheap stuff that doesn’t go the extra mile, we provide any great hardware and software that you need to connect with customers, partners and co-workers.

Anywhere365 is highly ambitious, which reflects in our tech stack and architecture as well as our culture and people’s DNA. Together we build strong connections and achieve great results. We love to celebrate our successes and look forward to celebrate yours soon.

Vinted is Europe's biggest pre-loved fashion marketplace, with 75+ million registered members in 18 countries. We want to make second-hand the first choice worldwide.

A team of 1,200+ people from Vinted's offices in Vilnius, Berlin, Prague, and Amsterdam develop and support our platform. We share a unique work culture that's based on aiming high, taking ownership, co-creating, caring, and growth.

Vinted is committed to building an inclusive workplace where people from all walks of life feel a sense of belonging. We welcome applications from all suitably qualified persons regardless of their race, colour, national origin, citizenship, sex, gender identity, sexual orientation, religion/beliefs, disability or age. We truly believe when we can be fully ourselves, we work better.

Vinted is on a mission to make sustainable consumption the first choice. Vinted is Europe's biggest pre-loved fashion marketplace, with 65 million members in 16 countries.

A team of over 1200 people from Vinted's offices in Vilnius, Berlin, Prague, Amsterdam, and Utrecht develop and support our platform. We share a unique work culture that's based on aiming high, taking ownership, co-creating, caring, and growing.

The Design System is an instrumental tool at Vinted for ensuring efficient development, high-quality standards, and maintaining consistency. As our new Product Designer, you will be focused on delivering better tools to our users – ~100 designers and engineers.

You'll work alongside other design system designers, 5 engineers and collaborate closely with Vinteds' designers, engineers, user researchers, and content designers.

In this position, you'll:
Join our Design System team to be the voice of our users, define their needs and goals, lead the design direction of our design system and its impact on the experience and visual design of Vinted products;
Become an authority on Vinted design language, setting standards for our design system and how systems thinking is embedded in Vinted design practice;
Own design of high-impact patterns, component designs, and cross-cutting features from inception to delivery, including engineering collaboration, rollout plans, usability testing, usage guidelines, and representation in design tools such as Figma;
In collaboration with your engineering and product counterparts, drive product discovery to identify new opportunities, strategize and evolve Design System architecture, shape and develop roadmaps for new initiatives;
Evangelize systems thinking and advocate for consistent, high-quality craft by providing design feedback and thought leadership, mentoring, and collaborating with other designers across Vinted organization;
Be a decision-maker regarding all things design in the Design System organization;
Lead the Design System education, training, and onboarding;
Be part of a Design Operations domain and report to the domain Design Director;
About you:
Significant experience in designing and shipping cross-platform products, from the web to native mobile;
Experience in building, owning, and maintaining design systems at scale;
A deep technical understanding of Design Systems (preferably at large scale) that bridges both Design and Engineering;
Strong visual, UI, and interaction skills — you're a champion for product excellence, an expert in platform-specific guidelines, and care about design craft and the details that elevate work from good to great;
Systems thinking with an ability to maintain simplicity in a growing design system and a clear sense of structure that is scalable; as well as a vision to see how all the parts fit together and how a small change can propagate throughout the system;
Thrive in complex and ambiguous spaces, comfortable working autonomously and proactively while also knowing when to bring others in to move things forward quickly;
Mastery of Figma and knowledge of other design tools such as Framer, Origami, etc.;
Passion for design systems and infectious energy when it comes to communicating the value of a design system to the broader organization;
Excellent communication skills, including excellent written and spoken English, to promote collaboration across a broad group of teams, including Design, Engineering, Product, and Branding;
You seek to develop your design leadership skills through mentorship and the way you elevate the quality of design – from actively seeking and providing feedback, communicating designs, and setting the standard for execution;
Work perks:
Opportunity to join our share options programme
Learning budget (10% from net yearly salary)
25 working days of holiday
Mental and emotional health support from Mindletic
Frequent team-building events
A personal budget for shopping on Vinted
An office in the centre of Amsterdam
Free daily lunch at the office, or reimbursement when working from home
Work anywhere in the EU for 90 days out of the year
Home office support (IT workstation equipment provided and a personal budget for home workplace furniture)

We want people to work from where they're most comfortable, which is why we're using a hybrid workplace model at Vinted for the foreseeable future.

Hybrid means that we encourage working from the office on Tuesdays and Wednesdays and the remainder of your time from either home or the office, but it's not required. You're welcome to work from either location all or some of the time, depending on what you think is best and safest for you, and how the Covid-19 situation is developing where you are.

The salary range for this position is 5270€ - 7575€ (gross) per month.

If this sounds interesting – you may well be just who we need!

Wil jij je studie afronden bij een internationaal bedrijf die gespecialiseerd is in het leveren van innovatieve digitale diensten en bedrijfsoplossingen? Wil je bestaande bedrijfsprocessen analyseren en automatiseren met behulp van Microsoft technologie? Dan is deze opdracht voor jou!

Afstudeeropdracht

Avanade is gespecialiseerd in het leveren van innovatieve digitale diensten en bedrijfsoplossingen. Ons succes is gebaseerd op ons vermogen om tot de kern van het probleem te komen en de beste digitale oplossingen voor onze klanten te vinden.

De afdeling Analytics & AI binnen Avanade bestaat uit vier practices: Data Engineering, Advanced Analytics, Analytics Experience en Analytics Architecture. Wij bieden studenten de mogelijkheid om hun HBO/WO opleiding bij Avanade af te ronden door het uitvoeren van een innovatieve onderzoeksopdracht/afstudeeropdracht binnen Avanade.

Het automatiseren van ons afstudeerprogramma staat bij deze opdracht centraal en sluit naadloos aan op jouw eigen ervaring - namelijk afstuderen bij Avanade! Het huidige stageprogramma binnen de Afdeling Analytics & AI bevat veel handmatige stappen. Dit is tijdrovend en kan gevoelig zijn voor fouten, zoals het missen van deadlines of miscommunicatie.

Het eerste doel van de opdracht is een procesanalyse en procesbeschrijving maken vanaf het moment dat er een stageplek beschikbaar komt tot het moment dat een student solliciteert en in dienst komt bij Avanade. Het tweede doel van de opdracht is het identificeren van de pijnpunten in het stageproces voor de afdeling Analytics en het proces automatiseren door gebruik te maken van de nieuwste Microsoft technologie. Deze opdracht heeft dus zowel een technisch als een consultant component en geeft jou een geweldige kans om kennis te maken met beide gebieden!

Dit zijn wij
Onze visie? ‘To advance the world through the power of people and Microsoft’. Elke dag zetten onze mensen zich in om met de nieuwste Microsoft-technologie onze klanten te helpen transformeren. Door de combinatie van een brede expertise van onze talentvolle mensen en een enorme passie voor Microsoft kunnen we onze klanten wereldwijd vooruit helpen op technologisch vlak en creëren we geweldige ervaringen & oplossingen.

Avanade is een internationaal IT-consultancybedrijf, waarbij mens en IT de krachten bundelen. Je zult jezelf herkennen in de 450 collega’s die rondlopen, maar ook zeker in de 40 andere stagiaires die jaarlijks stagelopen bij Avanade. We hebben veel passie voor en plezier in voor het werk dat we verrichten en hechten waarde aan een gezellige sfeer op de werkvloer. Met ontzettend veel talent voor Microsoft-technologie, is Avanade een unieke club waar veel ruimte is voor ontwikkeling en je onderdeel bent van een grote club professionals. Gezamenlijk met de andere stagiaires vorm je een enthousiaste groep & community binnen Avanade. Je kan meedoen aan veel leuke activiteiten zoals kennissessies tijdens de lunch, koffiemomenten met consultants en werkborrels! Daarnaast bieden we een aantal soft skilltrainingen speciaal voor de groep interns en de mogelijkheid tot het behalen van een Microsoft certificaat!

Wij zoeken jou omdat..


Je bent een HBO-student die op zoek is naar een leerzame en uitdagende afstudeerstage per 1 september 2023 op het gebied van IT-consultancy;
Je basiskennis hebt van Azure Power Platform, Power Pages, Power Apps, Power Automate en/of Power BI;
Je communicatief vaardig bent in zowel Nederlands als Engels;
Je affiniteit hebt met IT-consultancy & Microsoft;
Je gemotiveerd bent om een goed afstudeeronderzoek op te zetten, je proactief en zelfstandig te werk gaat en graag nieuwe collega's ontmoet!

Avanade biedt jou…


Een uitdagend en leerzaam stageprogramma. Aan het eind van je stage ben je een aantal (soft) skills rijker, heb je een goed beeld van Avanade en heb je waardevolle connecties opgebouwd;
De mogelijkheid om samen te werken in een team van professionals;
Goede ondersteuning van een (technisch) stagebegeleider, zowel inhoudelijk als procesmatig;
Een stagevergoeding (bachelor: 650 EUR/maand | master: 750 EUR/maand), een laptop en een prachtig (duurzaam) kantoor in Amsterdam-Zuid;
Budget voor het aanschaffen van een toetsenbord, muis en headset;
De mogelijkheid tot het behalen van een Microsoft certificaat, op onze kosten;
Twee vakantiedagen per maand;
Veel gezelligheid! Zo wordt er maandelijks door de Avanade Intern Committee een leuke activiteit georganiseerd, bieden we trainingen aan en is er maandelijks een borrel!

Word jij enthousiast van deze opdracht en zie je Avanade als een uitdagende en fijne stageplek? Solliciteer dan voor 17 april 2023! Twijfel je nog? Neem dan contact op met onze recruiter Floor Schipper (floor.schipper@avanade.com) om meer te horen over de mogelijkheden of voor een kop koffie!
